From 6af4dcd74cf641c125205b352b24f52616fcbd60 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: developers <developers@tuxbox-neutrino.org>
Date: Sat, 4 Apr 2026 23:57:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix: explicitly stop GUI service before rescue.target isolate
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

systemctl isolate rescue.target is asynchronous — it queues the
target transition but returns immediately. The subsequent
check_e2_stopped() poll could still find the GUI process running
because systemd had not yet sent SIGTERM to its cgroup.

Add explicit synchronous systemctl stop for both neutrino and
enigma2 services before the isolate call. systemctl stop blocks
until the service is actually down, ensuring the GUI process is
gone before the pivot_root sequence begins.
---
 ofgwrite.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/ofgwrite.c b/ofgwrite.c
index c5948d9..650bace 100644
--- a/ofgwrite.c
+++ b/ofgwrite.c
@@ -1326,6 +1326,11 @@ int umount_rootfs(int steps)
 	enum InitSystemEnum init_sys = detect_init_system();
 	if (init_sys == INIT_SYSTEMD)
 	{
+		my_printf("Stopping GUI service (systemd)\n");
+		// First, explicitly stop known GUI services synchronously.
+		// systemctl stop blocks until the service is actually stopped.
+		system("systemctl stop neutrino 2>/dev/null");
+		system("systemctl stop enigma2 2>/dev/null");
 		my_printf("Switching to rescue target (systemd)\n");
 		ret = system("systemctl isolate rescue.target");
 	}
